# Subsea Kill Sheet — Flutter

A single-file Flutter implementation of the **IWCF Subsea BOP Vertical Well Kill Sheet**
(API Field Units). Combines a fully interactive mobile entry form with a pixel-accurate
two-page A4 PDF export — all in one self-contained Dart file.

---

## Overview

This screen handles the additional complexity of a **subsea BOP** well-kill operation
compared to a surface BOP — specifically the marine riser, choke line length, choke line
friction (CLF), and the Initial Dynamic Casing Pressure at Kill Pump Rate. Every value
updates **live as you type**, and the sheet exports as an IWCF-layout PDF ready to share.

---

## What it does

- Full **kill-sheet entry form** across 8 collapsible sections
- **Live recalculation** on every keystroke — KMW, MAASP, ICP, FCP, CLF, IntDyn CP,
  L/100, volumes, strokes, times all update instantly
- **IWCF-layout A4 PDF export** (2 pages) — shared via OS share sheet
- **5 named save slots** — save, name, and reload any sheet; all stored as JSON on-device
- **Inline date picker** — calendar overlay anchored to the date field
- **Live subsea well diagram** — CustomPainter that draws marine riser, choke line, BOP,
  casing, open hole, drill string, and five colour-coded depth lines
- **Step-down chart** — auto-generated pressure vs. strokes graph from ICP → FCP

