## How it differs from the Surface Kill Sheet

The subsea BOP introduces physical differences that change the kill calculation:

| Difference | Effect on calculation |
|---|---|
| BOP is on the seabed, not at surface | A **marine riser** connects surface to seabed; its length and capacity form a separate volume segment |
| Fluid returns travel up a **choke line** alongside the riser | Choke line has its own length, capacity, and friction loss — CLF = Choke pressure − Riser pressure |
| Casing pressure reading is affected by CLF | A separate **Initial Dynamic Casing Pressure** (IntDyn CP = SICP − CLF) is calculated for kill pump rate |
| Pressure-drop term is called **L** instead of K | L = ICP − FCP; used for the step-down table and L/100 calculation |
| TVD reference for KMW | Uses **Hole TVD** (same as surface), but MAASP still uses Shoe TVD |

