## Sections

| # | Section | What you enter | What it calculates |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Formation Strength Data | FST (psi), Mud Weight at Test (ppg) | Max Allowable MW (C) — rounded down to 1 dp; Initial MAASP — rounded down to whole psi |
| 2 | Current Well Data | Marine riser length (ft), choke line length (ft), mud density, casing size/MD/TVD, hole size/MD/TVD | Live subsea well diagram with five colour-coded depth lines and dimension labels |
| 3 | Pump Data | Pump displacement (bbl/stk), SPM, Riser pressure (psi), Choke Line pressure (psi) | CLF = Choke − Riser; DPL = Riser pressure (used in ICP/FCP) |
| 4 | Volumetric Data & Pump Strokes | Lengths and capacities for DP, HWDP, DC, open hole annulus (×2 rows), casing annulus, choke line capacity, active surface volume (bbl), marine riser × DP capacity | Volume (bbl), pump strokes (ceiling), time (min, ceiling) for every segment; choke line and riser lengths carry over automatically from Section 2 |
| 5 | Kick Data & Kill Mud Weight | SIDPP (psi), SICP (psi), Pit Gain (bbl) | Kill Mud Weight (KMW) — rounded up to 1 dp |
| 6 | Circulating Pressures | (auto — uses values above) | ICP, FCP, L (ICP − FCP), L/100 strokes |
| 7 | Initial Dynamic Casing Pressure | (auto — uses SICP and CLF) | IntDyn CP at Kill Pump Rate = SICP − CLF |
| 8 | Step-Down Chart | (auto — uses ICP, FCP, DS strokes) | Pressure step-down table (every 100 strokes) and live line graph |

