## Volumetric Segments (Section 4)

The subsea sheet has more volume segments than the surface sheet:

| Segment | Label | Length source | Capacity source |
|---|---|---|---|
| Drill Pipe | (D) part | User input | User input |
| HWDP | (D) part | User input | User input |
| Drill Collars | (D) part | User input | User input |
| **DS Total** | **(D)** | — | Sum of above three |
| DC × Open Hole | (F) part | User input | User input |
| DP/HW × Open Hole | (F) part | User input | User input |
| **Open Hole Total** | **(F)** | — | Sum of above two |
| DP × Casing Annulus | (G) | User input | User input |
| Choke Line | (H) | **Auto from Section 2** | User input |
| **Total Annulus** | **(F+G+H = I)** | — | Sum of F, G, H |
| **Total Well System** | **(D+I = J)** | — | D + I |
| Active Surface Volume | (K) | — | User input (bbl direct) |
| **Total Active Fluid** | **(J+K)** | — | J + K |
| Marine Riser × DP | separate | **Auto from Section 2** | User input |

> Choke line length and marine riser length are entered **once** in Section 2 and
> automatically propagated into the volumetric table — no double entry required.

