## Well Diagram

The live diagram (`_SubseaWellDiagramPainter`) is a `CustomPainter` that draws:

- White background with surface line
- Casing (grey outline, light fill) from surface to shoe
- Open hole walls below shoe to TD
- Drill pipe (dark) inside casing; drill collars (wider) in open hole; bit at TD
- BOP housing above surface with two pressure gauges and a choke/kill line stub
- Casing shoe triangles and downward arrows at shoe and TD
- **Five colour-coded vertical depth lines** with value labels:

| Colour | Side | Represents |
|---|---|---|
| 🔴 Red | Left | Marine Riser length — dynamic dimension line with cap ticks and arrows |
| 🔵 Blue | Left | Full Hole TVD — static label at midpoint |
| 🟠 Orange | Left | Casing Shoe TVD — static label at midpoint |
| 🟢 Green | Left | Open Hole depth (Hole TVD − Shoe TVD) — static label |
| 🟣 Violet | Right | Choke Line length — dynamic dimension line with cap ticks and arrows |

The diagram repaints whenever csgTvd, holeTvd, marineRiserLen, or chokeLineLen changes.

---

## Step-Down Chart

`_StepDownChartPainter` builds the pressure-vs-strokes graph automatically once
ICP, FCP, and DS total strokes are all available:

- X-axis: 0 → DS total strokes in 100-stroke steps
- Y-axis: FCP → ICP (pressure in psi); pressure is floored at FCP
- Orange line connecting step points; green dots at each step
- Grid lines, axis labels, axis titles rendered via `TextPainter`
- Summary bar shows DS Strokes, ICP tag, and FCP tag above the data table

