## File structure

Everything lives in a single file — **`subsea_kill_sheet_screen.dart`**:

```
SubseaKillSheetPdfData         — immutable const data model; every PDF field in one object
PDF colour constants            — PdfColors aliases used across all section builders
PDF font globals                — _sKRegular, _sKBold, _sKItalic, _sKBoldItalic (loaded once)
_sT()                          — central TextStyle factory for PDF text
PDF primitive helpers           — _sBox(), _sBoxNoBorder(), _sUnderline() etc.
PDF section builders:
  _sBuildHeader()              — IWCF title + date/name underlines
  _sBuildFormationBlock()      — Formation Strength + MAASP formula layout
  _sBuildPumpBlock()           — Pump displacement + slow-pump rate table
                                 (Riser / Choke Line / CLF columns × Pump 1 & 2)
  _sBuildRightPanel()          — Current Well Data column + subsea schematic image
                                 with rotated overlay labels for all depth values
  _sBuildVolumeTable()         — Pre-recorded volume data table (all subsea segments)
  _sBuildKillSheetPage2()      — Full page 2 (kick data through graph section)
_generateSubseaKillSheetPdf()  — assembles both pages, loads fonts/image, returns bytes
SubseaKillSheetScreen          — StatefulWidget; the Navigator push target
_SubseaKillSheetScreenState    — all TextEditingControllers, computed strings,
                                  _recalcAll(), save/load, export, 8 section builders
_SubseaWellDiagramPainter      — CustomPainter: live subsea well schematic
_StepDownChartPainter          — CustomPainter: pressure step-down graph
_SubseaInlineDatePicker        — OverlayEntry calendar dropdown anchored to date field
_SubseaSlotPickerDialog        — modal dialog: 5-slot grid for save or open
_SubseaSlotLabelDialog         — modal dialog: name-entry before saving a slot
```

