## How to use

```dart
// Push the screen from anywhere in your app
Navigator.push(
  context,
  MaterialPageRoute(builder: (_) => const SubseaKillSheetScreen()),
);
```

**Typical workflow:**
1. Open the screen — today's date is pre-filled
2. Enter **Name** in the action bar
3. Fill **Section 1** — Formation Strength Test values → Max MW and MAASP appear instantly
4. Fill **Section 2** — Marine riser length, choke line length, well data → diagram updates live
5. Fill **Section 3** — Pump displacement, SPM, Riser pressure, Choke pressure → CLF auto-calculates
6. Fill **Section 4** — Lengths and capacities for all segments → volumes, strokes, times auto-fill;
   choke line and marine riser lengths carry over automatically from Section 2
7. Fill **Section 5** — SIDPP, SICP, Pit Gain → KMW appears
8. **Section 6** auto-fills ICP, FCP, L, L/100
9. **Section 7** auto-fills IntDyn CP at Kill Pump Rate
10. **Section 8** auto-generates the step-down table and chart
11. Tap **SAVE** to store the sheet, **EXPORT PDF** to share it

